	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well here is the <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/downloads/trace-f.jpg" class="postlink">front</a> and <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/downloads/trace-b.jpg" class="postlink">back</a> of a CNROM compatible board. Not particularly interested in the results of this one, but it happened to be laying around and should be easy to verify pinouts. 
<br />
<br />Scanned at 1200dpi, which seems sufficient, traces are 8+ pixels wide at that rez. This may prove to be harder than I thought, the traces aren't as distinct from the background as I thought, so trying to trace by chasing colors in a certain tolerance level probably won't work well. Working with the red channel only seems to give the most distinction between the traces and rest of the board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

